Interface MessageAction<S extends MessageProducer<S>>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - Where the message comes from.

    public interface MessageAction<S extends MessageProducer<S>>
    Allows to specify an action to be executed on top of a particular Message.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void execute(Message message, S source)
      Execute the action, typically on background.

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        void execute(Message message,
           S source)
        Execute the action, typically on background. Exceptions thrown here will be swallowed and, at the very best, logged.
        Parameters:
        message - Message that triggers the action.
        source - The source of the message.
